A simple latency test that measures the basic call dispatch delay of WCF.

To run the demo, first start the server:

$ server.exe

In a separate window, start the client:

$ client.exe

By default, the client and server use the loopback interface (127.0.0.1).
You can specify a different interface on the command line, for example:

$ server.exe 192.168.4.2

$ client.exe 192.168.4.2

By default server listens on port 10001 for binary messages,
and on port 10002 for SOAP messages. You can specify different
ports on the command line:

$ server.exe serverhost.xyz.com 11111 11112

$ client.exe serverhost.xyz.com 11111 11112

Under Vista, you must run the server as administrator.

